    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Presenting a museum-grade FD3S Mazda RX-7, a masterclass in 1990s weight-reduction engineering and kinematic balance. This specimen retains its original 13B-REW power plant, featuring the sophisticated sequential twin-turbocharger system with a perfectly calibrated pre-spool transition and stable boost pressure throughout the power band. The chassis is structurally immaculate, featuring factory-spec aluminum double-wishbone suspension that minimizes unsprung mass for surgical handling precision. The drivetrain is anchored by a precise five-speed longitudinal manual gearbox and a Torsen limited-slip differential, ensuring optimal torque distribution. All critical systems, including the complex vacuum-actuated charge-relief valves and cooling stack, have been maintained to exacting standards. With a pristine undercarriage and documented high-compression rotor housings, this unmolested example represents the zenith of Japanese performance heritage.",
